anycollseq.description: Fake fallback collating function for any unknown collating sequence

appendvfs.description: A VFS shim that allows an SQLite database to be appended onto the end of some other file, such as an executable

base64.description: Convert either direction between base64 blob and text

base85.description: Convert either direction between base85 blob and text

btreeinfo.description: btreeinfo virtual table that shows information about all btrees in an SQLite database file

cksumvfs.description: A VFS shim that writes a checksum on each page of an SQLite database file

closure.description: A virtual table that finds the transitive closure of a parent/child relationship in a real table

completion.description: A virtual table that returns suggested completions for a partial SQL input

csv.description: A virtual table for reading CSV files

decimal.description: Routines to implement arbitrary-precision decimal math

eval.description: Implements SQL function eval() which runs SQL statements recursively

fileio.description: Implements SQL functions readfile() and writefile(), and eponymous virtual type 'fsdir'

fuzzer.description: Virtual table that generates variations on an input word at increasing edit distances from the original

ieee754.description: functions for the exact display* and input of IEEE754 Binary64 floating-point numbers

memstat.description: Provides SQL access to the sqlite3_status64() and sqlite3_db_status() interfaces

nextchar.description: Finds all valid 'next' characters for a string given a vocabulary

noop.description: Implements noop() functions useful for testing

prefixes.description: Table valued function providing all prefixes of a string

regexp.description: Compact reasonably efficient posix extended regular expression matcher

sha1.description: SHA1 hash and query results hash

shathree.description: SHA3 hash and query results hash

spellfix.description: Search a large vocabulary for close matches

sqlite3_dbdump.description: Converts the content of a SQLite database into UTF-8 text SQL statements that can be used to exactly recreate the original database

sqlite3_dbhash.description: Computes SHA1 of the contents of a SQLite database

sqlite3_dbtotxt.description: Converts a binary file like a database into a friendly human readable text format

sqlite3_diff.description: Displays content differences between SQLite databases

sqlite3_expert.description: A simple system to propose useful indexes given a database and a set of SQL queries

sqlite3_getlock.description: Unix only shows if and who is holding a database lock

sqlite3_index_usage.description: Given a database and a log database, shows how many times each index is used

sqlite3_normalize.description: Normalizes SQL text so private information can be removed, and to identify structurally identical queries

sqlite3_offsets.description: Shows length and offset for every TEXT or BLOB for a column of a table

sqlite3_scrub.description: Makes a backup zeroing out all deleted content

sqlite3_showdb.description: Prints low level details about a database file

sqlite3_showjournal.description: Prints low level content of a journal

sqlite3_showlocks.description: Shows all posix advisory locks on a file

sqlite3_showshm.description: Shows low level content of shm and wal-index files

sqlite3_showstat4.description: Shows contents of stat4 index of a database

sqlite3_showtmlog.description: Makes human/csv readable output from a tmstmpvfs log file

sqlite3_showwal.description: Shows low level content of a WAL file

stmt.description: Virtual table with information about all prepared statements on a connection

stmtrand.description: Function that returns the same sequence of random integers is returned for each invocation of the statement

tmstmpvfs.description: VFS shim that writes timestamps and other tracing information to the reserved bytes of each page, and also generates corresponding log files

unionvtab.description: Virtual table combining underlying tables from other databases

vec1.description: Vector search.  !Experimental! !Under development! Loading on before 2013 CPU may crash process

vtablog.description: Virtual table printing diagnostic information for interactive analysis and debugging
